1 High er Education who offers a course or program in meteorology,
2 including federal or state research programs in the field of severe
3 weather, which shall include vehicles gathering atmospheric
4 conditions and radar vehicles;
5 3. "Qualified media outlet" shall mean a commercial television
6 or radio station licensed by the Federal Communication Commission
7 for the broadcast or transmission of television programming via
8 broadcast, cable, streaming, or other platforms as recognized by the
9 Federal Communications Commission; and
10 4. "Significant weather event" shall mean:
11 a. tornado or severe thunderstorm warning that partially
12 or wholly covers one or more counties located in the
13 State of Oklahoma issued by the National Weather
14 Service,
15 b. tornado or severe thunderstorm warned storms that are
16 located in any county within a neighboring state in
17 which that county borders the State of Oklahoma,
18 c. red flag fire warning issued by the National Weather
19 Service or the Oklahoma Forestry Services of the
20 Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and
21 Forestry, or
22 d. flash flood warning or flood warning issued by the
23 National Weather Service or the chief meteorologist
24 employed by a qualified media outlet.
