1 SECTION 4. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 19-303 of Title 47, unless there
3 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
5 for Service Oklahoma to be designated the "Severe Weather Tracker
6 Licensure Fund". The fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject
7 to fiscal year limitations. All monies accruing to the credit of
8 the fund are hereby appropriated and shall be budgeted and expended
9 by Service Oklahoma for the restricted purposes of the monies as
10 prescribed by law. Expenditures from the fund shall be made upon
11 warrants issued by the State Treasurer against claims filed as
12 prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of Management and
13 Enterprise Services for approval and payment.
14 SECTION 5. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 19-304 of Title 47, unless there
16 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 A. Primary vehicles utilized by a professional severe weather
18 tracker shall:
19 1. Display markings clearly identifying such vehicle as being
20 utilized for severe weather tracking and identifying the qualified
21 media outlet or qualified institution of higher education with which
22 the tracker is affiliated; and
23
24
HB2426 HFLR Page 8
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 2. Be authorized to be equipped with and to use the visual
2 signals described in Section 12-218 of Title 47 of the Oklahoma
3 Statutes.
4 B. Once the conditions of a significant weather event have been
5 met, a professional severe weather tracker may:
6 1. Activate the visual signals authorized for use in this act;
7 2. Be considered an authorized emergency vehicle for the
8 purposes of this act;
9 3. Travel upon roads, highways, and county roads closed by the
10 Department of Transportation, the Oklahoma Turnpike Authority, any
11 city or county, or any law enforcement agency by reason of
12 conditions triggered by the significant weather event;
13 4. Proceed past a red or stop signal or stop sign, but only
14 after slowing down as may be necessary for safe operation;
15 5. Exceed the maximum speed limits so long as speeding does not
16 endanger life or property;
17 6. Disregard regulations governing direction of movement; and
18 7. Disregard regulations governing turning in specified
19 directions.
20 C. The exemptions granted to a professional severe weather
21 tracker in this section shall apply only when the tracker is
22 properly and lawfully making use of flashing green and yellow lights
23 or a combination of flashing green and yellow lights meeting the
24 requirements of Section 12-218 of Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
HB2426 HFLR Page 9
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 D. The provisions of this section shall not limit the liability
2 of a professional severe weather tracker. The provisions of this
3 section shall not relieve the professional severe weather tracker
4 from the duty to drive with due regard for the safety of all
5 persons, nor shall such provisions protect the driver from the
6 consequences of reckless disregard for the safety of others.
7 E. Nothing in this section shall be construed to exempt a
8 professional severe weather tracker from obligation to yield right-
9 of-way and stop for superseding authorized emergency vehicles, as
10 prescribed in Section 1-103 of Title 47 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
11 SECTION 6. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
12 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 19-305 of Title 47, unless there
13 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
14 Any Professional Severe Weather Tracker found to be in violation
15 of the provisions of this act shall be subject to a fine, not to
16 exceed Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00), and revocation of his or her
17 license by Service Oklahoma.
18 Such fine or revocation shall be in addition to any criminal or
19 civil penalties that the Professional Severe Weather Tracker may be
20 subject to for any other violations of the laws of this state.
